  "description": [
    "THREE Say Big Bankers Deliberately Caused Crash in U S Stocks TO STALL OFF BIGGER ONE AT ELECTION TIME British Exchanges Hard Hit Financial Writers Say leader Special Service BERLIN Financial writers in the European jlress report that the sudden crash In the American stock exchanges was deliberately brought about by the big bankers for the purpose of preventing a bigger crash during the November elec tions Stock values had reached such a peak as a result of excessive specu lation that the margin of net in come from stocks had been reduced more and more the European writ ers sum up the situation More and more American securities went to foreign stock exchanges Use Drastic Method When the speculation reached alarming proportions the federal reserve banks raised their rates twice But when even this did not check speculation and it became evi dent that a crash might come dur ing the November elections the big bankers used drastic methods and deliberately staged a crash in June At the same time there was a great deal of opposition to the for eign and call loan policy of the fed eral reserve banks It was freely charged that productive industries were"
